		"description": "<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-dabe8b50-7fff-551b-ff0a-6d7f8411eb23\">You magically enhance the flavor of a dish, intensifying the herbs and spices to cover up the flavor of some additional ingredient. This addition could be poison, a potion&mdash;or the inclusion of vegetables. Any creature who consumes the food must make a Wisdom saving throw versus your spell save DC. On a success they may detect the added ingredient at the Narrator&rsquo;s discretion, and if appropriate, turn hostile. Creatures who fail don&rsquo;t notice the presence of the added ingredient. If a poison or a potion was the added ingredient, the creature then makes any relevant saving throw and experiences the effect of the item as normal.</span></p>",
